---
source: crates/tk/tests/scenarios.rs
expression: "p.run(&format!(\"{command} --help\"))"
---
Create a local Ticket or Epic

Usage: tk add [OPTIONS]

Options:
  -m, --message <MESSAGE>    Message paragraph; repeatable (-m title -m body ...). Conflicts with -F
  -F, --file <PATH>          Read the message from a file, or '-' for stdin
      --bug                  Create a bug Ticket (conflicts with --epic)
      --epic                 Create an Epic (conflicts with --bug, --priority, --parent)
  -P, --parent <EPIC>        Place the new Ticket under an Epic by Display ID or Alias
  -p, --priority <PRIORITY>  Set Priority (P0..P4). Tickets only
      --triage               Capture the Ticket in triage with no Priority, pending a decision (conflicts with --priority and --epic)
  -h, --help                 Print help
